G-MOE-COHERENCE — NORTHSTAR brick 2: the 35B-A3B generates coherent English on BOTH paths (2026-07-02)
======================================================================================================
GATE: greedy self-feed 16 tokens from a REAL prompt ("The capital of France is" = ids
760,6511,314,9338,369 in the 248320 vocab) through the stateless qwen36_forward, GGUF-direct
vs OK-container legs; detokenized via the SPTB vocab (tools: qwen36_gen_coherence.c harness +
sptb_detok.py).

DISCOVERY EN ROUTE: the M_QWEN36 gate's fixed prompt ids (785 3974 ...) are GIBBERISH in the
35B's 248320 vocab — they were minted for the 151k Qwen vocab (the gate is still valid: same
ids into both SP and the llama oracle = a fair bit-parity probe; but it is NOT a coherence
probe). This gate uses real-vocab ids; the SPTB encode round-trips exactly
('TheĠcapitalĠofĠFranceĠis' -> 760,6511,314,9338,369 -> same text).

LEG 1 — GGUF-direct (Q4_K_M):  **GREEN**
  "The capital of France is Paris, a city renowned for its rich history, culture, and
   iconic landmarks."          (16/16 tokens, flawless English, correct fact)

LEG 2 — OK-container (.sp-model): **GREEN**
  "The capital of France is Paris.\nA. True\nB. False\n<think>\nHere's a"
  (correct fact + grammatical English; quiz-format drift + <think> = normal for a
   reasoning-tuned base prompt without the chat template)

DIVERGENCE: both legs pick ' Paris' (tok 0 identical, 11751); they split at tok 1 on the
punctuation near-tie (',' vs '.') — the same cross-quant regime as the 2/3 round-trip
(G-MOE-FORWARD-35B leg 2). VERDICT: the OK container preserves the model. The right
container gates are exactly these (coherence + fact), not cross-quant bit-parity.

TIMING (the honest pain that motivates brick 3): stateless qwen36_forward recomputes ALL
positions per token — 16 tokens took 723s (GGUF) / 878s (spm) = ~0.02 tok/s proxy, with
per-forward cost growing 22->85s. llama.cpp CHATS this same model on this same CPU at
usable speed (kv-cached). **The missing piece is a qwen36 persistent-KV decode path**
(decode.c is gemma/qwen3-dense only today; GDN linear-attn state carries a per-layer
recurrent state instead of a KV window — the GDN recurrence is O(1)-state by construction,
which is exactly why this arch is attractive for the residency campaign).

NEXT (brick 3, pre-scoped):
1. qwen36 persistent-state decode: thread the GDN recurrent state + the 10 full-attn KV
   windows through a step function (the GDN math already exists in qwen36.c; the work is
   carrying state across calls instead of recomputing).
2. G-MOE-TOKS-CPU on the step function (the honest tok/s; llama-parity is the reference).
3. Then the GPU residency ladder (dp4a packed experts, hot-expert LRU vs 12GB).

TOOLS ADDED: lib/shannon-prime-system/tests/qwen36_gen_coherence.c (env QWEN36_PROMPT_IDS
override; stateless proxy timer), _faithful_corpus/sptb_detok.py (SPTB vocab parse +
byte-level BPE detok + greedy encode pattern in the receipt harness).
ENV: engine d517ac2 tree; build via the Stage-0 clang-cl chain (see G-SPEED-STAGE0-REBASE
gotchas: /MD + engine libs + sp_model_bridge.c TU). Raw: _gen_gguf2.out, _gen_spm.out.
